  "text": "In this paper we analyse clusters and networks of firms from two complementary theoretical frameworks. The first one draws upon the strategic decision-making approach to the theory of the firm, which analyses the governance of the economic system and defines the firm in terms of strategic planning [CITATION_1] . As a consequence, this approach sees both networks and clusters as organisational structures where firms relate with each other adjusting relationships on the basis of their economic power [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
